<!--l. 261--><p class="noindent" >[r][rt][width=3in,keepaspectratio]figure&#x02D9;newsyntax This version of gnuplot introduces command iteration and
block-structured if/else/while/do constructs. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">if (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-120000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">89</span><!--tex4ht:ref: if --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-7001"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">while (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-382000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">239</span><!--tex4ht:ref: while --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-7002"></a>, and <span 
class="cmbx-10">do (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-103000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">78</span><!--tex4ht:ref: do --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-7003"></a>. Simple
iteration is possible inside <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span>commands. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">iteration (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-122000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">90</span><!--tex4ht:ref: iteration --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-7004"></a>. General iteration spanning
multiple commands is possible using a block construct as shown below. For a related new feature, see the
<span 
class="cmbx-10">summation (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-33000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">34</span><!--tex4ht:ref: summation --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-7005"></a> expression type. Here is an example using several of these new syntax features:
<pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;multiplot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;layout</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2,2</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;fourier(k,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;x)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sin(3./2*k)/k</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;*</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2./3*cos(k*x)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;do</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;for</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;[power</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0:3]</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
