<!--l. 322--><p class="noindent" >
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-12000I"></a>New time/date handling</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-22"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-12001"></a>
<!--l. 325--><p class="noindent" >Gnuplot now tracks time to millisecond precision. Time formats have been modified to match this. The new built-in
function time() returns the current time of day according to the system clock. Example: print the current time to
msec precision <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
