<!--l. 1516--><p class="noindent" >
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-35000I"></a>User-defined variables and functions</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-68"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-35001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-35002"></a>
<!--l. 1524--><p class="noindent" >New user-defined variables and functions of one through twelve variables may be declared and used anywhere,
including on the <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>command itself.
<!--l. 1527--><p class="noindent" >User-defined function syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;func-name&#x003E;(</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;dummy1&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{,&#x003C;dummy2&#x003E;}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;...</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{,&#x003C;dummy12&#x003E;}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;expression&#x003E;</span>
<!--l. 1531--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 1534--><p class="noindent" >where <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>expression<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is defined in terms of <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>dummy1<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>through <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>dummy12<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>.
<!--l. 1536--><p class="noindent" >User-defined variable syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;variable-name&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;constant-expression&#x003E;</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 1540--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 1543--><p class="noindent" >Examples: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;w</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;q</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;floor(tan(pi/2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;-</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.1))</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;f(x)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sin(w*x)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sinc(x)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sin(pi*x)/(pi*x)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;delta(t)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(t</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;==</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ramp(t)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(t</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;?</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;t</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;:</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;min(a,b)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(a</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;b)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;?</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;a</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;:</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;b</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;comb(n,k)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;n!/(k!*(n-k)!)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;len3d(x,y,z)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sqrt(x*x+y*y+z*z)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;f(x)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sin(x*a),</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;a</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.2,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;f(x),</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;a</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.4,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;f(x)</span>
<!--l. 1556--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 1560--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;file</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"mydata.inp"</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;file(n)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sprintf("run_%d.dat",n)</span>
<!--l. 1563--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 1566--><p class="noindent" >The final two examples illustrate a user-defined string variable and a user-defined string function.
<a 
 id="dx1-35003"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-35004"></a>
<!--l. 1571--><p class="noindent" >Note that the variables <span 
class="cmbx-10">pi </span>(3.14159...) and <span 
class="cmbx-10">NaN </span>(IEEE <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>Not a Number<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>) are already defined. You
can redefine these to something else if you really need to. The original values can be recovered by
setting:
<!--l. 1576--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;NaN</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;GPVAL_NaN</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;pi</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;GPVAL_pi</span>
<!--l. 1579--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 1582--><p class="noindent" >Other variables may be defined under various gnuplot operations like mousing in interactive terminals or fitting; see
<span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot-defined variables (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-34000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">35</span><!--tex4ht:ref: gnuplot-defined variables --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-35005"></a> for details.
<!--l. 1585--><p class="noindent" >You can check for existence of a given variable V by the exists(<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>V<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>) expression. For example <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;a</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;10</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;if</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(exists("a"))</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;print</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"a</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;is</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;defined"</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;if</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(!exists("b"))</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;print</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"b</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;is</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;not</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;defined"</span>
<!--l. 1592--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 1595--><p class="noindent" >Valid names are the same as in most programming languages: they must begin with a letter, but subsequent
characters may be letters, digits, or <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>_<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>.
<!--l. 1598--><p class="noindent" >Each function definition is made available as a special string-valued variable with the prefix &#8217;GPFUN_&#8217;.
<!--l. 1601--><p class="noindent" >Example: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;label</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;GPFUN_sinc</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;at</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;graph</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;.05,.95</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 1605--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 1608--><p class="noindent" >See <span 
class="cmbx-10">show functions (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-226000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">155</span><!--tex4ht:ref: show functions --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-35006"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">functions (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-175000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">115</span><!--tex4ht:ref: functions --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-35007"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot-defined variables (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-34000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">35</span><!--tex4ht:ref: gnuplot-defined variables --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-35008"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">macros (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-56000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">49</span><!--tex4ht:ref: macros --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-35009"></a>,
<span 
class="cmbx-10">value (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-28000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">32</span><!--tex4ht:ref: value --></a><span 
