<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-44000I"></a>Linecolor variable</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-86"></a>
<!--l. 1945--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">lc variable </span>tells the program to use the value read from one column of the input data as a linetype index, and use
the color belonging to that linetype. This requires a corresponding additional column in the <span 
class="cmbx-10">using </span>specifier. Text
colors can be set similarly using <span 
class="cmbx-10">tc variable</span>.
<!--l. 1950--><p class="noindent" >Examples: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;#</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;Use</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;third</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;column</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;of</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;data</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;to</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;assign</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;colors</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;to</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;individual</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;points</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;data&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1:2:3</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;with</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;points</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;lc</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;variable</span>
