<!--l. 2043--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 2046--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind </span>allows defining or redefining a hotkey, i.e. a sequence of gnuplot commands which will be executed when a
certain key or key sequence is pressed while the driver&#8217;s window has the input focus. Note that <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind </span>is only
available if gnuplot was compiled with <span 
class="cmbx-10">mouse </span>support and it is used by all mouse-capable terminals. A
user-specified binding supersedes any builtin bindings, except that <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>space<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>and &#8217;q&#8217; cannot normally be rebound.
For an exception, see <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind space (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-49000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">45</span><!--tex4ht:ref: bind space --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-48004"></a>.
<!--l. 2054--><p class="noindent" >Mouse buttons cannot be rebound.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 2056--><p class="noindent" >You get the list of all hotkeys by typing <span 
class="cmbx-10">show bind </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind </span>or by typing the hotkey &#8217;h&#8217; in the graph
window.
<!--l. 2059--><p class="noindent" >Key bindings are restored to their default state by <span 
class="cmbx-10">reset bind</span>.
<!--l. 2061--><p class="noindent" >Note that multikey-bindings with modifiers must be given in quotes.
<!--l. 2063--><p class="noindent" >Normally hotkeys are only recognized when the currently active plot window has focus. <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind allwindows </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">key</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">... </span>(short form: <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind all </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">key</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span><span 
class="cmbx-10">...</span>) causes the binding for <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>key<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>to apply to all gnuplot plot windows, active or
not. In this case gnuplot variable MOUSE_KEY_WINDOW is set to the ID of the originating window, and may be
used by the bound command.
