<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-49000I"></a>Bind space</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-96"></a>
<!--l. 2164--><p class="noindent" >If gnuplot was built with configuration option &#8211;enable-raise-console, then typing <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>space<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>in the plot
window raises gnuplot&#8217;s command window. This hotkey can be changed to ctrl-space by starting gnuplot
as &#8217;gnuplot -ctrlq&#8217;, or by setting the XResource &#8217;gnuplot*ctrlq&#8217;. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">x11 command-line-options</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-487000IV"><span 
class="cmbx-10">313</span><!--tex4ht:ref: x11 command-line-options --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-49001"></a>.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-50000I"></a>Mouse variables</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-98"></a>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 2171--><p class="noindent" >When <span 
class="cmbx-10">mousing </span>is active, clicking in the active window will set several user variables that can be
accessed from the gnuplot command line. The coordinates of the mouse at the time of the click are
stored in MOUSE_X MOUSE_Y MOUSE_X2 and MOUSE_Y2. The mouse button clicked, and any
meta-keys active at that time, are stored in MOUSE_BUTTON MOUSE_SHIFT MOUSE_ALT and
MOUSE_CTRL. These variables are set to undefined at the start of every plot, and only become
defined in the event of a mouse click in the active plot window. To determine from a script if the mouse
has been clicked in the active plot window, it is sufficient to test for any one of these variables being
defined.
<!--l. 2182--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;something&#8217;</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;pause</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mouse</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;if</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(defined(MOUSE_BUTTON))</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;call</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;something_else&#8217;;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;\</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;else</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;print</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"No</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mouse</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;click."</span>
