<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-64000II"></a>Boxplot</h3>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-125"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-64001"></a>
<!--l. 2834--><p class="noindent" >[r][rt][width=3in,keepaspectratio]figure&#x02D9;boxplot Boxplots are a common way to represent a statistical distribution of
values. Quartile boundaries are determined such that 1/4 of the points have a value equal or less than the first
quartile boundary, 1/2 of the points have a value equal or less than the second quartile (median) value, etc. A box is
drawn around the region between the first and third quartiles, with a horizontal line at the median value.
Whiskers extend from the box to user-specified limits. Points that lie outside these limits are drawn
individually.
<!--l. 2843--><p class="noindent" >Examples
<!--l. 2846--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;#</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;Place</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;a</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;boxplot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;at</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;x</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;coordinate</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1.0</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;representing</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;y</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;values</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;in</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;column</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;5</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;data&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(1.0):5</span>
<!--l. 2849--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 2853--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;#</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;Same</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;but</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;suppress</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;outliers</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;and</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;force</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;width</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;of</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;boxplot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;to</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.3</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;style</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;boxplot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;nooutliers</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;data&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(1.0):5:(0.3)</span>
<!--l. 2857--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 2860--><p class="noindent" >By default only one boxplot is produced that represents all y values from the second column of the using
specification. However, an additional (fourth) colunm can be added to the specification. If present, the values of that
column will be interpreted as the discrete levels of a factor variable. As many boxplots will be drawn as there are
levels in the factor variable. The separation between these boxplots is 1.0 by default, but it can be changed by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">style boxplot separation</span>. By default, the value of the factor variable is shown as a tic label below (or above) each
boxplot.
<!--l. 2869--><p class="noindent" >Example
<!--l. 2872--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;#</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;Suppose</span><span 
