class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;data&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(1.0):5:(0):2</span>
<!--l. 2877--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 2880--><p class="noindent" >The default width of the box can be set via <span 
class="cmbx-10">set boxwidth </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">width</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>or may be specified as an optional 3rd column
in the <span 
class="cmbx-10">using </span>clause of the plot command. The first and third columns (x coordinate and width) are normally
provided as constants rather than as data columns.
<!--l. 2885--><p class="noindent" >By default the whiskers extend from the ends of the box to the most distant point whose y value lies within 1.5
times the interquartile range. By default outliers are drawn as circles (point type 7). The width of the bars at the
end of the whiskers may be controlled using <span 
class="cmbx-10">set bars</span>.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 2890--><p class="noindent" >These default properties may be changed using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set style boxplot </span>command. See <span 
