<!--l. 2893--><p class="noindent" >
<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-65000II"></a>Boxxyerrorbars</h3>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-127"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-65001"></a>
<!--l. 2901--><p class="noindent" >[r][rt][width=3in,keepaspectratio]figure&#x02D9;boxxyerrorbars The <span 
class="cmbx-10">boxxyerrorbars </span>style is only relevant to 2D data
plotting. It is similar to the <span 
class="cmbx-10">xyerrorbars </span>style except that it draws rectangular areas rather than simple crosses. It
uses either 4 or 6 basic columns of input data. Additional input columns may be used to provide information such as
variable line or fill color (see <span 
class="cmbx-10">rgbcolor variable (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-45000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">42</span><!--tex4ht:ref: rgbcolor variable --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-65002"></a>).
<!--l. 2909--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;4</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;columns:</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;x</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;y</span><span 
