<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-70000II"></a>Filledcurves</h3>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-137"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-70001"></a>
<!--l. 3160--><p class="noindent" >[r][rt][width=3in,keepaspectratio]figure&#x02D9;filledcurves The <span 
class="cmbx-10">filledcurves </span>style is only relevant to 2D plotting. Three
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
variants are possible. The first two variants require either a function or two columns of input data, and may be
further modified by the options listed below.
<!--l. 3165--><p class="noindent" >Syntax:
<!--l. 3168--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;...</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;with</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;filledcurves</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;[option]</span>
<!--l. 3170--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 3173--><p class="noindent" >where the option can be one of the following
<!--l. 3176--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;[closed</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{above</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;below}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{x1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;x2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;y1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;y2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;r}[=&#x003C;a&#x003E;]</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xy=&#x003C;x&#x003E;,&#x003C;y&#x003E;]</span>
<!--l. 3179--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 3182--><p class="noindent" >The first variant, <span 
class="cmbx-10">closed</span>, treats the curve itself as a closed polygon. This is the default if there are two columns of
input data.
<!--l. 3185--><p class="noindent" >The second variant is to fill the area between the curve and a given axis, a horizontal or vertical line, or a
point.
