<!--l. 3617--><p class="noindent" >[r][rt][width=3in,keepaspectratio]figure&#x02D9;rgb3D Each pixel (data point) of the input 2D image will become a
rectangle or parallelipiped in the plot. The coordinates of each data point will determine the center
of the parallelipiped. That is, an M x N set of data will form an image with M x N pixels. This is
different from the pm3d plotting style, where an M x N set of data will form a surface of (M-1) x (N-1)
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
elements. The scan directions for a binary image data grid can be further controlled by additional
keywords. See <span 
