class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-82003"></a>). The example below generates a 2D plot with text labels
constructed from the city whose name is taken from column 1 of the input file, and whose geographic
coordinates are in columns 4 and 5. The font size is calculated from the value in column 3, in this case the
population.
<!--l. 3732--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;CityName(String,Size)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sprintf("{/=%d</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;%s}",</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;Scale(Size),</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;String)</span>
