<!--l. 3939--><p class="noindent" >[r][rt][width=3in,keepaspectratio]figure&#x02D9;xerrorbars The <span 
class="cmbx-10">xerrorbars </span>style is only relevant to 2D data plots.
<span 
class="cmbx-10">xerrorbars </span>is like <span 
class="cmbx-10">points</span>, except that a horizontal error bar is also drawn. At each point (x,y), a line is drawn from
(xlow,y) to (xhigh,y) or from (x-xdelta,y) to (x+xdelta,y), depending on how many data columns are provided. A
tic mark is placed at the ends of the error bar (unless <span 
class="cmbx-10">set bars </span>is used &#8212; see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set bars (p.</span><span 
