<h1 class="partHead"><span class="titlemark">Part&#x00A0;III<br /></span><a 
 id="x1-99000III"></a>Commands</h1>
<a 
 id="dx1-99001"></a>
<!--l. 4175--><p class="noindent" >This section lists the commands acceptable to <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>in alphabetical order. Printed versions of this document
contain all commands; the text available interactively may not be complete. Indeed, on some systems there may be
no commands at all listed under this heading.
<!--l. 4180--><p class="noindent" >Note that in most cases unambiguous abbreviations for command names and their options are permissible, i.e., <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">p</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">f(x) w li</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>instead of <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">plot f(x) with lines</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>.
<!--l. 4184--><p class="noindent" >In the syntax descriptions, braces (<span 
class="cmsy-10">{}</span>) denote optional arguments and a vertical bar (<span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span>) separates mutually exclusive
choices.
<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-100000III"></a>Cd</h3>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-196"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-100001"></a>
<!--l. 4191--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">cd </span>command changes the working directory.
<!--l. 4193--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cd</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;&#x003C;directory-name&#x003E;&#8217;</span>
<!--l. 4197--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 4200--><p class="noindent" >The directory name must be enclosed in quotes.
<!--l. 4202--><p class="noindent" >Examples: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cd</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;subdir&#8217;</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cd</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;".."</span>
<!--l. 4207--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 4210--><p class="noindent" >It is recommended that Windows users use single-quotes, because backslash [<span 
class="cmsy-10">\</span>] has special significance inside
double-quotes and has to be escaped. For example, <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cd</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"c:\newdata"</span>
<!--l. 4216--><p class="noindent" ></pre> fails, but <pre class="prettyprint">
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cd</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;c:\newdata&#8217;</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cd</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"c:\\newdata"</span>
<!--l. 4223--><p class="noindent" ></pre> work as expected.
<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-101000III"></a>Call</h3>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-198"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-101001"></a>
<!--l. 4231--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">call </span>command is identical to the load command with one exception: you can have up to ten additional
parameters to the command (delimited according to the standard parser rules) which can be substituted into the
lines read from the file. As each line is read from the <span 
class="cmbx-10">call</span>ed input file, it is scanned for the sequence <span 
class="cmbx-10">$ </span>(dollar-sign)
followed by a digit (0&#8211;9). If found, the sequence is replaced by the corresponding parameter from the <span 
class="cmbx-10">call </span>command
line. If the parameter was specified as a string in the <span 
class="cmbx-10">call </span>line, it is substituted without its enclosing quotes.
Sequence <span 
class="cmbx-10">$# </span>is replaced by the number of passed parameters. <span 
class="cmbx-10">$ </span>followed by any character will be that character;
e.g. use <span 
class="cmbx-10">$$ </span>to get a single <span 
class="cmbx-10">$</span>. Providing more than ten parameters on the <span 
class="cmbx-10">call </span>command line will cause an error. A
parameter that was not provided substitutes as nothing. Files being <span 
class="cmbx-10">call</span>ed may themselves contain <span 
class="cmbx-10">call </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">load</span>
commands.
<!--l. 4245--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;call</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"&#x003C;input-file&#x003E;"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;parameter-0&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;parm-1&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;...</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;parm-9&#x003E;</span>
<!--l. 4249--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 4252--><p class="noindent" >The name of the input file must be enclosed in quotes, and it is recommended that parameters are
similarly enclosed in quotes (future versions of gnuplot may treat quoted and unquoted arguments
differently).
<!--l. 4256--><p class="noindent" >Example:
<!--l. 4258--><p class="noindent" >If the file &#8217;calltest.gp&#8217; contains the line: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;print</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"argc=$#</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p0=$0</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p1=$1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p2=$2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p3=$3</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p4=$4</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p5=$5</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p6=$6</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p7=x$7x"</span>
<!--l. 4262--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 4265--><p class="noindent" >entering the command: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;call</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;calltest.gp&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"abcd"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1.2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;+</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"&#8217;quoted&#8217;"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;--</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"$2"</span>
<!--l. 4269--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 4272--><p class="noindent" >will display: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;argc=7</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p0=abcd</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p1=1.2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p2=+</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p3=&#8217;quoted&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p4=-</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p5=-</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p6=$2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;p7=xx</span>
<!--l. 4276--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 4279--><p class="noindent" >NOTE: there is a clash in syntax with the datafile <span 
class="cmbx-10">using </span>callback operator. Use <span 
class="cmbx-10">$$n </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">column(n) </span>to access
column n from a datafile inside a <span 
class="cmbx-10">call</span>ed datafile plot.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-102000III"></a>Clear</h3>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-200"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-102001"></a>
<!--l. 4287--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">clear </span>command erases the current screen or output device as specified by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set output</span>. This usually generates a
formfeed on hardcopy devices. Use <span 
class="cmbx-10">set terminal </span>to set the device type.
<!--l. 4291--><p class="noindent" >For some terminals <span 
class="cmbx-10">clear </span>erases only the portion of the plotting surface defined by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set size</span>, so for these it can be
used in conjunction with <span 
class="cmbx-10">set multiplot </span>to create an inset.
<!--l. 4295--><p class="noindent" >Example: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;multiplot</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;sin(x)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;origin</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.5,0.5</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.4,0.4</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
