<a 
 id="dx1-122002"></a>
<!--l. 5134--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset </span>commands may optionally contain an iteration clause. This has the effect of
executing the basic command multiple times, each time re-evaluating any expressions that make use of the iteration
control variable. Iteration of arbitrary command sequences can be requested using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">do </span>command. Two forms of
iteration clause are currently supported:
<!--l. 5142--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
