<!--l. 5850--><p class="noindent" >To avoid this, you can use the <span 
class="cmbx-10">fixmin</span>/<span 
class="cmbx-10">fixmax </span>feature of the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set autoscale </span>command, which turns off the
automatic extension of the axis range up to the next tic mark.
<!--l. 5854--><p class="noindent" >Label coordinates and text can also be read from a data file (see <span 
class="cmbx-10">labels (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-82000II"><span 
class="cmbx-10">69</span><!--tex4ht:ref: labels --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-148008"></a>).
<!--l. 5856--><p class="noindent" >
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-149000III"></a>Every</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-294"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-149001"></a>
<!--l. 5865--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">every </span>keyword allows a periodic sampling of a data set to be plotted.
<!--l. 5867--><p class="noindent" >In the discussion a <span 
