<!--l. 6671--><p class="noindent" ><span class="likeparagraphHead"><a 
 id="x1-167000III"></a>Xticlabels</span>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-330"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-167001"></a>
Axis tick labels can be generated via a string function, usually taking a data column as an argument. The simplest
form uses the data column itself as a string. That is, xticlabels(N) is shorthand for xticlabels(stringcolumn(N)). This
example uses the contents of column 3 as x-axis tick labels.
<!--l. 6683--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;datafile&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;xcol&#x003E;:&#x003C;ycol&#x003E;:xticlabels(3)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;with</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;plotstyle&#x003E;</span>
<!--l. 6685--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 6688--><p class="noindent" >Axis tick labels may be generated for any of the plot axes: x x2 y y2 z. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">ticlabels(</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">labelcol</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">) </span>specifiers must
come after all of the data coordinate specifiers in the <span 
class="cmbx-10">using </span>portion of the command. For each data point which has
a valid set of X,Y[,Z] coordinates, the string value given to xticlabels() is added to the list of xtic labels at
the same X coordinate as the point it belongs to. <span 
class="cmbx-10">xticlabels() </span>may be shortened to <span 
class="cmbx-10">xtic() </span>and so
on.
<!--l. 6696--><p class="noindent" >Example:
<!--l. 6699--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;splot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"data"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2:4:6:xtic(1):ytic(3):ztic(6)</span>
<!--l. 6701--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 6704--><p class="noindent" >In this example the x and y axis tic labels are taken from different columns than the x and y coordinate values. The
z axis tics, however, are generated from the z coordinate of the corresponding point.
<!--l. 6708--><p class="noindent" >Example:
<!--l. 6711--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
