class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;$3</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;10.</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;?</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"A"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;:</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"B"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;)</span>
<!--l. 6713--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 6716--><p class="noindent" >This example shows the use of a string-valued function to generate x-axis tick labels. Each point in the
data file generates a tick mark on x labeled either <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>A<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>or <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>B<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>depending on the value in column
3.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
