<!--l. 7123--><p class="noindent" >This is example does exactly the same thing as the previous example, but uses the string iterator form of the
command rather than an integer iterator.
<!--l. 7126--><p class="noindent" >
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-179000III"></a>Title</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-354"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-179001"></a>
<!--l. 7134--><p class="noindent" >By default each plot is listed in the key by the corresponding function or file name. You can give an explicit plot
title instead using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">title </span>option.
<!--l. 7137--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;title</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;text&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;notitle</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;[&#x003C;ignored</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;text&#x003E;]</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;title</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;columnheader</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;title</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;columnheader(N)</span>
<!--l. 7142--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 7145--><p class="noindent" >where <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>text<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is a quoted string or an expression that evaluates to a string. The quotes will not be shown in the
key.
<!--l. 7148--><p class="noindent" >There is also an option that will interpret the first entry in a column of input data (i.e. the column header) as a text
field, and use it as the key title. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">datastrings (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-21000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">25</span><!--tex4ht:ref: datastrings --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-179002"></a>. This can be made the default by specifying <span 
class="cmbx-10">set key</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">autotitle columnhead</span>.
<!--l. 7153--><p class="noindent" >The line title and sample can be omitted from the key by using the keyword <span 
class="cmbx-10">notitle</span>. A null title (<span 
class="cmbx-10">title &#8217; &#8217;</span>) is
equivalent to <span 
class="cmbx-10">notitle</span>. If only the sample is wanted, use one or more blanks (<span 
class="cmbx-10">title &#8217; &#8217;</span>). If <span 
class="cmbx-10">notitle </span>is followed by a
string this string is ignored.
<!--l. 7158--><p class="noindent" >If <span 
class="cmbx-10">key autotitles </span>is set (which is the default) and neither <span 
class="cmbx-10">title </span>nor <span 
class="cmbx-10">notitle </span>are specified the line title is the function
name or the file name as it appears on the <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>command. If it is a file name, any datafile modifiers specified will be
included in the default title.
<!--l. 7163--><p class="noindent" >The layout of the key itself (position, title justification, etc.) can be controlled by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set key</span>. Please see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set key</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-231000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">159</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set key --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-179003"></a> for details.
<!--l. 7166--><p class="noindent" >Examples:
<!--l. 7168--><p class="noindent" >This plots y=x with the title &#8217;x&#8217;: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;x</span>
