<!--l. 7516--><p class="noindent" >
<h3 class="likesectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-186000III"></a>Replot</h3>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-368"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-186001"></a>
<!--l. 7521--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">replot </span>command without arguments repeats the last <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot </span>command. This can be useful for viewing a
plot with different <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span>options, or when generating the same plot for several devices.
<!--l. 7525--><p class="noindent" >Arguments specified after a <span 
class="cmbx-10">replot </span>command will be added onto the last <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot </span>command (with an implied
&#8217;,&#8217; separator) before it is repeated. <span 
class="cmbx-10">replot </span>accepts the same arguments as the <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot </span>commands except that
ranges cannot be specified. Thus you can use <span 
class="cmbx-10">replot </span>to plot a function against the second axes if the previous
command was <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>but not if it was <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot</span>.
<!--l. 7532--><p class="noindent" >N.B. &#8212; use of
<!--l. 7535--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;-&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;...</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;replot</span>
<!--l. 7537--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 7540--><p class="noindent" >is not recommended, because it will require that you type in the data all over again. In most cases
you can use the <span 
class="cmbx-10">refresh </span>command instead, which will redraw the plot using the data previously read
in.
<!--l. 7544--><p class="noindent" >Note that <span 
class="cmbx-10">replot </span>does not work in <span 
class="cmbx-10">multiplot </span>mode, since it reproduces only the last plot rather than the entire
screen.
