<!--l. 8236--><p class="noindent" >Various bits or combinations of bits may be added together in the command.
<!--l. 8238--><p class="noindent" >The default is 31, which is all four sides for <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, and base and z axis for <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot</span>.
<!--l. 8241--><p class="noindent" >In 2D plots the border is normally drawn on top of all plots elements (<span 
class="cmbx-10">front</span>). If you want the border to be drawn
behind the plot elements, use <span 
class="cmbx-10">set border back</span>.
<!--l. 8245--><p class="noindent" >Using the optional <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>line_style<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>line_type<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>line_width<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>specifiers, the way the border lines are drawn can
be influenced (limited by what the current terminal driver supports).
<!--l. 8249--><p class="noindent" >For <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, tics may be drawn on edges other than bottom and left by enabling the second axes &#8211; see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set xtics</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-335000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">220</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xtics --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-199003"></a> for details.
<!--l. 8252--><p class="noindent" >If a <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot </span>draws only on the base, as is the case with <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">unset surface; set contour base</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, then the verticals and
the top are not drawn even if they are specified.
<!--l. 8256--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set grid </span>options &#8217;back&#8217;, &#8217;front&#8217; and &#8217;layerdefault&#8217; also control the order in which the border lines are drawn
with respect to the output of the plotted data.
<!--l. 8260--><p class="noindent" >Examples:
<!--l. 8262--><p class="noindent" >Draw default borders: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;border</span>
<!--l. 8266--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 8269--><p class="noindent" >Draw only the left and bottom (<span 
class="cmbx-10">plot</span>) or both front and back bottom left (<span 
