<!--l. 8630--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 8633--><p class="noindent" >Color box position can be <span 
class="cmbx-10">default </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">user</span>. If the latter is specified the values as given with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">origin </span>and
<span 
class="cmbx-10">size </span>subcommands are used. The box can be drawn after (<span 
class="cmbx-10">front</span>) or before (<span 
class="cmbx-10">back</span>) the graph or the
surface.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 8637--><p class="noindent" >The orientation of the color gradient can be switched by options <span 
class="cmbx-10">vertical </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">horizontal</span>.
<!--l. 8640--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">origin x, y </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">size x, y </span>are used only in combination with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">user </span>option. The x and y values are
interpreted as screen coordinates by default, and this is the only legal option for 3D plots. 2D plots,
including splot with <span 
class="cmbx-10">set view map</span>, allow any coordinate system to be specified. Try for example:
<pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;colorbox</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;horiz</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;user</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;origin</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;.1,.02</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;.8,.04</span>
<!--l. 8647--><p class="noindent" ></pre> which will draw a horizontal gradient somewhere at the bottom of the graph.
<!--l. 8651--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">border </span>turns the border on (this is the default). <span 
class="cmbx-10">noborder </span>turns the border off. If an positive integer
argument is given after <span 
class="cmbx-10">border</span>, it is used as a line style tag which is used for drawing the border, e.g.:
<pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;style</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;line</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2604</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;linetype</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;-1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;linewidth</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;.4</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;colorbox</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;border</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2604</span>
<!--l. 8658--><p class="noindent" ></pre> will use line style <span 
class="cmbx-10">2604</span>, a thin line with the default border color (-1) for drawing the border. <span 
class="cmbx-10">bdefault </span>(which is
the default) will use the default border line style for drawing the border of the color box.
<!--l. 8664--><p class="noindent" >The axis of the color box is called <span 
class="cmbx-10">cb </span>and it is controlled by means of the usual axes commands, i.e.
<span 
class="cmbx-10">set/unset/show </span>with <span 
class="cmbx-10">cbrange</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">[m]cbtics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">format cb</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">grid [m]cb</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">cblabel</span>, and perhaps even <span 
class="cmbx-10">cbdata</span>,
<span 
class="cmbx-10">[no]cbdtics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">[no]cbmtics</span>.
<!--l. 8669--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">set colorbox </span>without any parameter switches the position to default. <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset colorbox </span>resets the default
parameters for the colorbox and switches the colorbox off.
<!--l. 8673--><p class="noindent" >See also help for <span 
class="cmbx-10">set pm3d (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-265000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">182</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set pm3d --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-204002"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">set palette (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-274000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">187</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set palette --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-204003"></a>, <span 
