<!--l. 8741--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 8744--><p class="noindent" >In order to draw contours, the data should be organized as <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>grid data<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>. In such a file all the points for a single
y-isoline are listed, then all the points for the next y-isoline, and so on. A single blank line (a line containing no
characters other than blank spaces and a carriage return and/or a line feed) separates one y-isoline from the next.
See also <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot datafile (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-371000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">231</span><!--tex4ht:ref: splot datafile --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-206007"></a>.
