<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-213000III"></a>Set datafile commentschars</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-422"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-213001"></a>
<!--l. 8913--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set datafile commentschars </span>command allows you to tell <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>what characters are used in a data file to
denote comments. Gnuplot will ignore rest of the line behind the specified characters if either of them is the first
non-blank character on the line.
<!--l. 8918--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;datafile</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;commentschars</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{"&#x003C;string&#x003E;"}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;datafile</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;commentschars</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;unset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;commentschars</span>
<!--l. 8924--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 8927--><p class="noindent" >Default value of the string is <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>#!<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>on VMS and <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>#<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>otherwise.
<!--l. 8929--><p class="noindent" >Then, the following line in a data file is completely ignored <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;#</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;3</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;4</span>
<!--l. 8933--><p class="noindent" ></pre> but the following <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;#</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;3</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;4</span>
<!--l. 8939--><p class="noindent" ></pre> produces rather unexpected plot unless <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;datafile</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;missing</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;#&#8217;</span>
<!--l. 8945--><p class="noindent" ></pre> is specified as well.
<!--l. 8949--><p class="noindent" >Example: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;datafile</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;commentschars</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"#!%"</span>
<!--l. 8953--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
