<!--l. 9581--><p class="noindent" >Except for the non-numerical formats, these may be preceded by a <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>0<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>(<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>zero<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, not <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>oh<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>) to pad the field length
with leading zeroes, and a positive digit, to define the minimum field width (which will be overridden if the specified
width is not large enough to contain the number). The %S format also accepts a precision specifier so that fractional
seconds can be written. There is a 24-character limit to the length of the printed text; longer strings will be
truncated.
