<!--l. 10152--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10156--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;l/bm</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;c/bm</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;r/bm</span>
<!--l. 10158--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10162--><p class="noindent" >Keywords <span 
class="cmbx-10">above </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">over </span>are synonymous with <span 
class="cmbx-10">tmargin</span>. For version compatibility, <span 
class="cmbx-10">above </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">over </span>without an
additional l/c/r or stack direction keyword uses <span 
class="cmbx-10">center </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">horizontal</span>. Keywords <span 
class="cmbx-10">below </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">under </span>are
synonymous with <span 
class="cmbx-10">bmargin</span>. For compatibility, <span 
class="cmbx-10">below </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">under </span>without an additional l/c/r or stack direction
keyword uses <span 
class="cmbx-10">center </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">horizontal</span>. A further compatibility issue is that <span 
class="cmbx-10">outside </span>appearing without
an additional t/b/c or stack direction keyword uses <span 
class="cmbx-10">top</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">right </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">vertical </span>(i.e., the same as t/rm
above).
<!--l. 10171--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>position<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>can be a simple x,y,z as in previous versions, but these can be preceded by one of five keywords
(<span 
class="cmbx-10">first</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">second</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">graph</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">screen</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">character</span>) which selects the coordinate system in which the position
of the first sample line is specified. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">coordinates (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-20000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">24</span><!--tex4ht:ref: coordinates --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-232001"></a> for more details. The effect of <span 
class="cmbx-10">left</span>,
<span 
class="cmbx-10">right</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">top</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">bottom</span>, and <span 
class="cmbx-10">center </span>when <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>position<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is given is to align the key as though it were text
positioned using the label command, i.e., <span 
class="cmbx-10">left </span>means left align with key to the right of <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>position<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>,
etc.
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-233000III"></a>Key samples</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-462"></a>
<!--l. 10184--><p class="noindent" >By default, each plot on the graph generates a corresponding entry in the key. This entry contains a plot title and a
sample line/point/box of the same color and fill properties as used in the plot itself. The font and textcolor
properties control the appearance of the individual plot titles that appear in the key. Setting the textcolor to
<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>variable<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>causes the text for each key entry to be the same color as the line or fill color for that plot. This was the
default in some earlier versions of gnuplot.
<!--l. 10192--><p class="noindent" >The length of the sample line can be controlled by <span 
class="cmbx-10">samplen</span>. The sample length is computed as the sum of the tic
length and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>sample_length<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>times the character width. <span 
class="cmbx-10">samplen </span>also affects the positions of point samples in
the key since these are drawn at the midpoint of the sample line, even if the sample line itself is not
drawn.
<!--l. 10198--><p class="noindent" >The vertical spacing between lines is controlled by <span 
class="cmbx-10">spacing</span>. The spacing is set equal to the product of the pointsize,
the vertical tic size, and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>vertical_spacing<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>. The program will guarantee that the vertical spacing is no smaller
than the character height.
<!--l. 10203--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>width_increment<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is a number of character widths to be added to or subtracted from the length of the string.
This is useful only when you are putting a box around the key and you are using control characters in the text.
<span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>simply counts the number of characters in the string when computing the box width; this allows you to
correct it.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-234000III"></a>Label</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-464"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-234001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-234002"></a>
<!--l. 10220--><p class="noindent" >Arbitrary labels can be placed on the plot using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set label </span>command.
<!--l. 10222--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;label</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{&#x003C;tag&#x003E;}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{"&#x003C;label</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;text&#x003E;"}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{at</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;position&#x003E;}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
