<!--l. 10294--><p class="noindent" >If a <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>pointstyle<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is given, using keywords <span 
class="cmbx-10">lt</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">pt </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">ps</span>, see <span 
class="cmbx-10">style (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-180000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">120</span><!--tex4ht:ref: style --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-234010"></a>, a point with the given style and color
of the given line type is plotted at the label position and the text of the label is displaced slightly. This option is
used by default for placing labels in <span 
class="cmbx-10">mouse </span>enhanced terminals. Use <span 
class="cmbx-10">nopoint </span>to turn off the drawing of a point
near the label (this is the default).
<!--l. 10301--><p class="noindent" >The displacement defaults to 1,1 in <span 
class="cmbx-10">pointsize </span>units if a <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>pointstyle<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is given, 0,0 if no <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>pointstyle<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is given. The
displacement can be controlled by the optional <span 
class="cmbx-10">offset </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">offset</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>where <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>offset<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is specified by either x,y or x,y,z,
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
and may be preceded by <span 
class="cmbx-10">first</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">second</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">graph</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">screen</span>, or <span 
class="cmbx-10">character </span>to select the coordinate system. See
<span 
class="cmbx-10">coordinates (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-20000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">24</span><!--tex4ht:ref: coordinates --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-234011"></a> for details.
<!--l. 10307--><p class="noindent" >If one (or more) axis is timeseries, the appropriate coordinate should be given as a quoted time string according to
the <span 
class="cmbx-10">timefmt </span>format string. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">set xdata (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-330000III"><span 
