<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-235000III"></a>Linetype</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-466"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-235001"></a>
<!--l. 10422--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set linetype </span>command allows you to redefine the basic linetypes used for plots. The command options are
identical to those for <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>set style line<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>. Unlike line styles, redefinitions by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set linetype </span>are persistent; they are not
affected by <span 
class="cmbx-10">reset</span>.
<!--l. 10427--><p class="noindent" >For example, linetypes one and two default to red and green. If you redefine them like this:
<!--l. 10431--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;linetype</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;lw</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;lc</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;rgb</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"blue"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;pointtype</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;6</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;linetype</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;lw</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;lc</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;rgb</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"forest-green"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;pointtype</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;8</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 10434--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10437--><p class="noindent" >everywhere that uses lt 1 will now get a thick blue line rather than a thin red line (the previous default meaning of
lt 1). This includes uses such as the definition of a temporary linestyle derived from the base linetype
1.
<!--l. 10441--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">Note</span>: This command is new to gnuplot version 4.6. It supersedes a rather cryptic command in version 4.2 <span 
