<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-237000III"></a>Loadpath</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-470"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-237001"></a>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 10500--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">loadpath </span>setting defines additional locations for data and command files searched by the <span 
class="cmbx-10">call</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">load</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot </span>and
<span 
class="cmbx-10">splot </span>commands. If a file cannot be found in the current directory, the directories in <span 
class="cmbx-10">loadpath </span>are
tried.
<!--l. 10505--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;loadpath</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{"pathlist1"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{"pathlist2"...}}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;loadpath</span>
<!--l. 10510--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10513--><p class="noindent" >Path names may be entered as single directory names, or as a list of path names separated by a platform-specific
path separator, eg. colon (&#8217;:&#8217;) on Unix, semicolon (&#8217;;&#8217;) on DOS/Windows/OS/2 platforms. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">show</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">loadpath</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">save </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">save set </span>commands replace the platform-specific separator with a space character (&#8217;
&#8217;).
<!--l. 10519--><p class="noindent" >If the environment variable GNUPLOT_LIB is set, its contents are appended to <span 
class="cmbx-10">loadpath</span>. However, <span 
class="cmbx-10">show</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">loadpath </span>prints the contents of <span 
class="cmbx-10">set loadpath </span>and GNUPLOT_LIB separately. Also, the <span 
class="cmbx-10">save </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">save set</span>
commands ignore the contents of GNUPLOT_LIB.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-238000III"></a>Locale</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-472"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-238001"></a>
<!--l. 10529--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">locale </span>setting determines the language with which <span 
class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x,y,z</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">}{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">d,m</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">}</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">tics </span>will write the days and
months.
<!--l. 10532--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;locale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{"&#x003C;locale&#x003E;"}</span>
<!--l. 10536--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10539--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>locale<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>may be any language designation acceptable to your installation. See your system documentation for the
available options. The command <span 
class="cmbx-10">set locale </span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"" </span>will try to determine the locale from the LC_TIME, LC_ALL, or
LANG environment variables.
<!--l. 10544--><p class="noindent" >To change the decimal point locale, see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set decimalsign (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-215000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">146</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set decimalsign --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-238002"></a>. To change the character encoding to the
current locale, see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set encoding (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-218000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">150</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set encoding --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-238003"></a>.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-239000III"></a>Logscale</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-474"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-239001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-239002"></a>
<!--l. 10559--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;axes&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{&#x003C;base&#x003E;}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;unset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;axes&#x003E;</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span>
<!--l. 10565--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10568--><p class="noindent" >where <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>axes<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>may be any combinations of <span 
class="cmbx-10">x</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">x2</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">y</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">y2</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">z</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">cb</span>, and <span 
class="cmbx-10">r </span>in any order. <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>base<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is the base of the log
scaling (default is base 10). If no axes are specified, the command affects all axes except <span 
class="cmbx-10">r</span>. The command <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">logscale </span>turns off log scaling for all axes.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 10573--><p class="noindent" >Examples:
<!--l. 10575--><p class="noindent" >To enable log scaling in both x and z axes: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xz</span>
<!--l. 10579--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10582--><p class="noindent" >To enable scaling log base 2 of the y axis: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;y</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span>
<!--l. 10586--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10589--><p class="noindent" >To enable z and color log axes for a pm3d plot: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;zcb</span>
<!--l. 10593--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 10596--><p class="noindent" >To disable z axis log scaling: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;unset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;z</span>
<!--l. 10600--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-240000III"></a>Macros</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-476"></a>
<!--l. 10608--><p class="noindent" >If command line macro substitution is enabled, then tokens in the command line of the form
@<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>stringvariablename<span 
