<!--l. 10680--><p class="noindent" >
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-242000III"></a>Margin</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-480"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-242001"></a>
<!--l. 10688--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">margin </span>is the distance between the plot border and the outer edge of the canvas. The size of the margin is
chosen automatically, but can be overridden by the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set margin </span>commands. <span 
class="cmbx-10">show margin </span>shows the current
settings. To alter the distance between the inside of the plot border and the data in the plot itself, see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set offsets</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-260000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">180</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set offsets --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-242002"></a>.
<!--l. 10694--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
