<!--l. 10772--><p class="noindent" >The options <span 
class="cmbx-10">noruler </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">ruler </span>switch the ruler off and on, the latter optionally setting the origin at the given
coordinates. While the ruler is on, the distance in user units from the ruler origin to the mouse is displayed
continuously. By default, toggling the ruler has the key binding &#8217;r&#8217;.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 10777--><p class="noindent" >The option <span 
class="cmbx-10">polardistance </span>determines if the distance between the mouse cursor and the ruler is also shown in polar
coordinates (distance and angle in degrees or tangent (slope)). This corresponds to the default key binding
&#8217;5&#8217;.
<a 
 id="dx1-243004"></a>
<!--l. 10782--><p class="noindent" >Choose the option <span 
class="cmbx-10">labels </span>to define persistent gnuplot labels using Button 2. The default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">nolabels</span>, which makes
Button 2 draw only a temporary label at the mouse position. Labels are drawn with the current setting of
<span 
class="cmbx-10">mouseformat</span>. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">labeloptions </span>string is passed to the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set label </span>command. The default is <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>point pointstyle 1<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>
which will plot a small plus at the label position. Temporary labels will disappear at the next <span 
class="cmbx-10">replot </span>or mouse zoom
operation. Persistent labels can be removed by holding the Ctrl-Key down while clicking Button 2
on the label&#8217;s point. The threshold for how close you must be to the label is also determined by the
<span 
class="cmbx-10">pointsize</span>.
<!--l. 10792--><p class="noindent" >If the option <span 
class="cmbx-10">verbose </span>is turned on the communication commands are shown during execution. This option can also
be toggled by hitting <span 
class="cmbx-10">6 </span>in the driver&#8217;s window. <span 
class="cmbx-10">verbose </span>is off by default.
<!--l. 10796--><p class="noindent" >Press &#8217;h&#8217; in the driver&#8217;s window for a short summary of the mouse and key bindings. This will also display user
defined bindings or <span 
class="cmbx-10">hotkeys </span>which can be defined using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind </span>command, see help for <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-48000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">43</span><!--tex4ht:ref: bind --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-243005"></a>. Note, that
user defined <span 
class="cmbx-10">hotkeys </span>may override the default bindings. See also help for <span 
class="cmbx-10">bind (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-48000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">43</span><!--tex4ht:ref: bind --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-243006"></a> and <span 
class="cmbx-10">label</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-234000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">163</span><!--tex4ht:ref: label --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-243007"></a>.
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-244000III"></a>Doubleclick</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-484"></a>
<!--l. 10805--><p class="noindent" >The doubleclick resolution is given in milliseconds and used for Button 1, which copies the current mouse position to
the <span 
class="cmbx-10">clipboard</span>. The default value is 300 ms. Setting the value to 0 ms triggers the copy on a single
click.
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-245000III"></a>Mouseformat</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-486"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-245001"></a>
<!--l. 10815--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set mouse format </span>command specifies a format string for sprintf() which determines how the
mouse cursor [x,y] coordinates are printed to the plot window and to the clipboard. The default is <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>%
#g<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>.
<!--l. 10819--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">set mouse clipboardformat </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set mouse mouseformat </span>are used for formatting the text on
Button1 and Button2 actions &#8211; copying the coordinates to the clipboard and temporarily annotating the
mouse position. An integer argument selects one of the format options in the table below. A string
argument is used as a format for sprintf() in option 6 and should contain two float specifiers. Example:
<pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8216;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mouse</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mouseformat</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"mouse</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;x,y</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;=</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;%5.2g,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;%10.3f"&#8216;.</span>
<!--l. 10828--><p class="noindent" ></pre> Use <span 
class="cmbx-10">set mouse mouseformat </span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"" </span>to turn this string off again.
<!--l. 10832--><p class="noindent" >The following formats are available:
<!--l. 10835--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">0</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;default</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(same</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;as</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
