<!--l. 10918--><p class="noindent" >For some terminals, no plot is displayed until the command <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset multiplot </span>is given, which causes the entire page
to be drawn and then returns gnuplot to its normal single-plot mode. For other terminals, each separate <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot</span>
command produces an updated display, either by redrawing all previous ones and the newly added plot, or by just
adding the new plot to the existing display.
<!--l. 10925--><p class="noindent" >The area to be used by the next plot is not erased before doing the new plot. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">clear </span>command can be used to do
this if wanted, as is typically the case for <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>inset<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>plots.
<!--l. 10929--><p class="noindent" >Any labels or arrows that have been defined will be drawn for each plot according to the current size and origin
(unless their coordinates are defined in the <span 
class="cmbx-10">screen </span>system). Just about everything else that can be <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span>is applied to
each plot, too. If you want something to appear only once on the page, for instance a single time stamp, you&#8217;ll need
to put a <span 
class="cmbx-10">set time</span>/<span 
class="cmbx-10">unset time </span>pair around one of the <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">splot </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">replot </span>commands within the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">multiplot</span>/<span 
class="cmbx-10">unset multiplot </span>block.
<!--l. 10937--><p class="noindent" >The multiplot title is separate from the individual plot titles, if any. Space is reserved for it at the top of the page,
spanning the full width of the canvas.
<!--l. 10941--><p class="noindent" >The commands <span 
class="cmbx-10">set origin </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set size </span>must be used to correctly position each plot if no layout is
specified or if fine tuning is desired. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">set origin (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-261000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">180</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set origin --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-249003"></a> and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set size (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-292000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">197</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set size --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-249004"></a> for details of their
usage.
