<!--l. 11002--><p class="noindent" >
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-250000III"></a>Mx2tics</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-496"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-250001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-250002"></a>
<!--l. 11014--><p class="noindent" >Minor tic marks along the x2 (top) axis are controlled by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set mx2tics</span>. Please see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set mxtics (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-251000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">175</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set mxtics --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-250003"></a>.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-251000III"></a>Mxtics</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-498"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-251001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-251002"></a>
<!--l. 11028--><p class="noindent" >Minor tic marks along the x axis are controlled by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set mxtics</span>. They can be turned off with <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset mxtics</span>. Similar
commands control minor tics along the other axes.
<!--l. 11032--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mxtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{&#x003C;freq&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;default}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;unset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mxtics</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mxtics</span>
<!--l. 11038--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 11041--><p class="noindent" >The same syntax applies to <span 
class="cmbx-10">mytics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">mztics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">mx2tics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">my2tics </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">mcbtics</span>.
<!--l. 11044--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>freq<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is the number of sub-intervals (NOT the number of minor tics) between major tics (the default for a linear
axis is either two or five depending on the major tics, so there are one or four minor tics between major tics).
Selecting <span 
class="cmbx-10">default </span>will return the number of minor ticks to its default value.
<!--l. 11050--><p class="noindent" >If the axis is logarithmic, the number of sub-intervals will be set to a reasonable number by default (based upon the
length of a decade). This will be overridden if <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>freq<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is given. However the usual minor tics (2, 3, ..., 8, 9
between 1 and 10, for example) are obtained by setting <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>freq<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>to 10, even though there are but nine
sub-intervals.
<!--l. 11056--><p class="noindent" >To set minor tics at arbitrary positions, use the (<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>label<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>pos<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; &#x003C;</span>level<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, ...) form of <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">z</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">}</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">tics </span>with
<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>label<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>empty and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>level<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>set to 1.
<!--l. 11059--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set m</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">z</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">}</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">tics </span>commands work only when there are uniformly spaced major tics. If all major tics
were placed explicitly by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">z</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">}</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">tics</span>, then minor tic commands are ignored. Implicit major
tics and explicit minor tics can be combined using <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">z</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">}</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">tics </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set </span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">x2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">y2</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">|</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">z</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">}</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">tics</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">add</span>.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 11065--><p class="noindent" >Examples: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
