<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-277000III"></a>Functions</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-550"></a>
<!--l. 12115--><p class="noindent" >Use <span 
class="cmbx-10">set palette functions </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">Rexpr</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">, </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">Gexpr</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">, </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">Bexpr</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>to define three formulae for the R(gray), G(gray)
and B(gray) mapping. The three formulae may depend on the variable <span 
class="cmbx-10">gray </span>which will take values in [0,1] and
should also produce values in [0,1]. Please note that <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>Rexpr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>might be a formula for the H-value if HSV color space
has been chosen (same for all other formulae and color spaces).
