<!--l. 12147--><p class="noindent" >
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-278000III"></a>Cubehelix</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-552"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-278001"></a>
<!--l. 12153--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>cubehelix<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>option defines a family of palettes in which color (hue) varies along the standard color wheel
while at the same time the net intensity increases monotonically as the gray value goes from 0 to 1.
<pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;D</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;A</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;Green</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(2011)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;http://arxiv.org/abs/1108.5083</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 12159--><p class="noindent" ></pre> <span 
class="cmbx-10">start </span>defines the starting point along the color wheel in radians. <span 
class="cmbx-10">cycles </span>defines how many color wheel cycles span
the palette range. Larger values of <span 
class="cmbx-10">saturation </span>produce more saturated color; saturation <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>1 may lead to clipping of
the individual RGB components and to intensity becoming non-monotonic. The palette is also affected by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">palette gamma</span>. The default values are <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;palette</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cubehelix</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;start</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.5</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;cycles</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;-1.5</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;saturation</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;palette</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;gamma</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1.5</span>
<!--l. 12171--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12174--><p class="noindent" >
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-279000III"></a>File</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-554"></a>
<!--l. 12179--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">set palette file </span>is basically a <span 
class="cmbx-10">set palette defined (</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">gradient</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">) </span>where <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>gradient<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is read from a datafile.
Either 4 columns (gray,R,G,B) or just three columns (R,G,B) have to be selected via the <span 
class="cmbx-10">using </span>data file modifier. In
the three column case, the line number will be used as gray. The gray range is automatically rescaled to [0,1]. The
file is read as a normal data file, so all datafile modifiers can be used. Please note, that <span 
class="cmbx-10">R </span>might actually be e.g. <span 
class="cmbx-10">H </span>if
HSV color space is selected.
<!--l. 12188--><p class="noindent" >As usual <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>filename<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>may be <span 
class="cmbx-10">&#8217;-&#8217; </span>which means that the data follow the command inline and are terminated by a
single <span 
class="cmbx-10">e </span>on a line of its own.
<!--l. 12191--><p class="noindent" >Use <span 
class="cmbx-10">show palette gradient </span>to display the gradient.
<!--l. 12193--><p class="noindent" >Examples:
<!--l. 12195--><p class="noindent" >Read in a palette of RGB triples each in range [0,255]: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;palette</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;file</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8217;some-palette&#8217;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;($1/255):($2/255):($3/255)</span>
<!--l. 12199--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12202--><p class="noindent" >Equidistant rainbow (blue-green-yellow-red) palette: <pre class="prettyprint">
