class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;record=64</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1:2:3</span>
<!--l. 12219--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12223--><p class="noindent" >
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-280000III"></a>Gamma correction</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-556"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-280001"></a>
<!--l. 12230--><p class="noindent" >For gray mappings gamma correction can be turned on by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set palette gamma </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">gamma</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>. <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>gamma<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>defaults to
1.5 which is quite suitable for most terminals.
<!--l. 12234--><p class="noindent" >The gamma correction is applied to the cubehelix color palette family, but not to other palette coloring schemes.
However, you may easily implement gamma correction for explicit color functions.
<!--l. 12238--><p class="noindent" >Example: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;palette</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;model</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;RGB</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
