<!--l. 12453--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-287000III"></a>Raxis</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-570"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-287001"></a>
<!--l. 12460--><p class="noindent" >The commands <span 
class="cmbx-10">set raxis </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset raxis </span>toggle whether the polar axis is drawn separately from grid lines and the
x axis. If the minimum of the current rrange is non-zero (and not autoscaled), then a white circle is drawn at the
center of the polar plot to indicate that the plot lines and axes do not reach 0. The axis line is drawn using the
same line type as the plot border. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">polar (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-284000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">194</span><!--tex4ht:ref: polar --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-287002"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">rrange (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-289000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">196</span><!--tex4ht:ref: rrange --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-287003"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">rtics (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-290000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">196</span><!--tex4ht:ref: rtics --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-287004"></a>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">set grid</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-227000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">155</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set grid --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-287005"></a>.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-288000III"></a>Rmargin</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-572"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-288001"></a>
<!--l. 12472--><p class="noindent" >The command <span 
class="cmbx-10">set rmargin </span>sets the size of the right margin. Please see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set margin (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-242000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">170</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set margin --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-288002"></a> for
details.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-289000III"></a>Rrange</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-574"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-289001"></a>
<!--l. 12482--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set rrange </span>command sets the range of the radial coordinate for a graph in polar mode. This has the effect of
setting both xrange and yrange as well. The resulting xrange and yrange are both [-(rmax-rmin) : +(rmax-rmin)].
However if you later change the x or y range, for example by zooming, this does not change rrange,
so data points continue to be clipped against rrange. Autoscaling of rmin always results in rmin =
0.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-290000III"></a>Rtics</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-576"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-290001"></a>
<!--l. 12496--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set rtics </span>command places tics along the polar axis. These will only be shown in polar plot mode. The tics
and labels are drawn to the right of the origin. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">mirror </span>keyword causes them to be drawn also
to the left of the origin. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">polar (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-284000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">194</span><!--tex4ht:ref: polar --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-290002"></a>, and see <span 
class="cmbx-10">set xtics (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-335000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">220</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set xtics --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-290003"></a> for discussion of other
keywords.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-291000III"></a>Samples</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-578"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-291001"></a>
<!--l. 12508--><p class="noindent" >The sampling rate of functions, or for interpolating data, may be changed by the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set samples </span>command.
<!--l. 12511--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;samples</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;samples_1&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{,&#x003C;samples_2&#x003E;}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;samples</span>
<!--l. 12516--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12519--><p class="noindent" >By default, sampling is set to 100 points. A higher sampling rate will produce more accurate plots, but will take
longer. This parameter has no effect on data file plotting unless one of the interpolation/approximation options is
used. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot smooth (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-152000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">104</span><!--tex4ht:ref: plot smooth --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-291002"></a> re 2D data and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set cntrparam (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-203000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">138</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set cntrparam --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-291003"></a> and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set dgrid3d (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-216000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">147</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set dgrid3d --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-291004"></a> re 3D
data.
<!--l. 12525--><p class="noindent" >When a 2D graph is being done, only the value of <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>samples_1<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is relevant.
<!--l. 12527--><p class="noindent" >When a surface plot is being done without the removal of hidden lines, the value of samples specifies the number of
samples that are to be evaluated for the isolines. Each iso-v line will have <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>sample_1<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>samples and each iso-u line
will have <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>sample_2<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>samples. If you only specify <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>samples_1<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>samples_2<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>will be set to the same value as
<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>samples_1<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>. See also <span 
class="cmbx-10">set isosamples (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-230000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">158</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set isosamples --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-291005"></a>.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-292000III"></a>Size</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-580"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-292001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-292002"></a>
<!--l. 12546--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{{no}square</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ratio</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;r&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;noratio}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{&#x003C;xscale&#x003E;,&#x003C;yscale&#x003E;}</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span>
<!--l. 12551--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12554--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>xscale<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>yscale<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>values are scale factors for the size of the plot, which includes the graph, labels, and
margins.
<!--l. 12557--><p class="noindent" >Important note: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;In</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;earlier</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;versions</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;of</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;gnuplot,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;some</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;terminal</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;types</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;used</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;values</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;from</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#8216;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size&#8216;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;to</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;control</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;also</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;of</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;output</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;canvas;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;others</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;did</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;not.</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;In</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;version</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;4.6</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;almost</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;all</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;terminals</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;now</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;follow</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;the</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;following</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;convention:</span>
<!--l. 12563--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12566--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">set term </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">terminal</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">_type</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span><span 
class="cmbx-10">size </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">XX</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">, </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">YY</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>controls the size of the output file, or <span 
class="cmbx-10">canvas</span>. Please see
individual terminal documentation for allowed values of the size parameters. By default, the plot will fill this
canvas.
<!--l. 12570--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">set size </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">XX</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">, </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">YY</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>scales the plot itself relative to the size of the canvas. Scale values less than 1 will cause
the plot to not fill the entire canvas. Scale values larger than 1 will cause only a portion of the plot to fit on the
canvas. Please be aware that setting scale values larger than 1 may cause problems on some terminal
types.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 12576--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">ratio </span>causes <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>to try to create a graph with an aspect ratio of <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>r<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>(the ratio of the y-axis length to the
x-axis length) within the portion of the plot specified by <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>xscale<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>yscale<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>.
<!--l. 12580--><p class="noindent" >The meaning of a negative value for <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>r<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is different. If <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>r<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>=-1, gnuplot tries to set the scales so that the
unit has the same length on both the x and y axes. This is equivalent to <span 
class="cmbx-10">set view equal xy</span>. See
<span 
class="cmbx-10">set view equal (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-321000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">214</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set view equal --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-292003"></a>. If <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>r<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>=-2, the unit on y has twice the length of the unit on x, and so
on.
<!--l. 12585--><p class="noindent" >The success of <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>in producing the requested aspect ratio depends on the terminal selected. The graph area
will be the largest rectangle of aspect ratio <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>r<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>that will fit into the specified portion of the output (leaving
adequate margins, of course).
<!--l. 12590--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">square </span>is a synonym for <span 
class="cmbx-10">ratio 1</span>.
<!--l. 12592--><p class="noindent" >Both <span 
class="cmbx-10">noratio </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">nosquare </span>return the graph to the default aspect ratio of the terminal, but do not return
<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>xscale<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>or <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>yscale<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>to their default values (1.0).
<!--l. 12596--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">ratio </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">square </span>have no effect on 3D plots, but do affect 3D projections created using <span 
class="cmbx-10">set view map</span>. See also
<span 
class="cmbx-10">set view equal (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-321000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">214</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set view equal --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-292004"></a>, which forces the x and y axes of a 3D onto the same scale.
<!--l. 12600--><p class="noindent" >Examples:
<!--l. 12602--><p class="noindent" >To set the size so that the plot fills the available canvas: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1,1</span>
<!--l. 12606--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12609--><p class="noindent" >To make the graph half size and square use: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;square</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.5,0.5</span>
<!--l. 12613--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12616--><p class="noindent" >To make the graph twice as high as wide use: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ratio</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span>
<!--l. 12620--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12623--><p class="noindent" >
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-293000III"></a>Style</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-582"></a>
<!--l. 12628--><p class="noindent" >Default plotting styles are chosen with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set style data </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set style function </span>commands. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">plot with</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">(p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-180000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">120</span><!--tex4ht:ref: plot with --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-293001"></a> for information about how to override the default plotting style for individual functions and data sets. See
<span 
class="cmbx-10">plotting styles (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-61000II"><span 
class="cmbx-10">53</span><!--tex4ht:ref: plotting styles --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-293002"></a> for a complete list of styles.
<!--l. 12633--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;style</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;function</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;style&#x003E;</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;style</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;data</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;style&#x003E;</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;style</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;function</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;show</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;style</span><span 
