class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{border</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{lt}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{lc</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;colorspec&#x003E;}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;noborder}</span>
<!--l. 12880--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 12883--><p class="noindent" >The default fillstyle is <span 
class="cmbx-10">empty</span>.
<!--l. 12885--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">solid </span>option causes filling with a solid color, if the terminal supports that. The <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>density<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>parameter specifies
the intensity of the fill color. At a <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>density<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>of 0.0, the box is empty, at <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>density<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>of 1.0, the inner area is
of the same color as the current linetype. Some terminal types can vary the density continuously;
others implement only a few levels of partial fill. If no <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>density<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>parameter is given, it defaults to
1.
<!--l. 12893--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">pattern </span>option causes filling to be done with a fill pattern supplied by the terminal driver. The kind and
number of available fill patterns depend on the terminal driver. If multiple datasets using filled boxes are plotted,
the pattern cycles through all available pattern types, starting from pattern <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>n<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, much as the line type cycles for
multiple line plots.
<!--l. 12899--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">empty </span>option causes filled boxes not to be filled. This is the default.
<!--l. 12901--><p class="noindent" >By default, <span 
class="cmbx-10">border</span>, the box is bounded by a solid line of the current linetype. <span 
class="cmbx-10">border </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">colorspec</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>allows you to
change the color of the border. <span 
class="cmbx-10">noborder </span>specifies that no bounding lines are drawn.
<!--l. 12904--><p class="noindent" ><span class="likeparagraphHead"><a 
 id="x1-298000III"></a>Set style fill transparent</span>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-592"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-298001"></a>
Some terminals support the attribute <span 
class="cmbx-10">transparent </span>for filled areas. In the case of transparent solid fill areas, the
<span 
class="cmbx-10">density </span>parameter is interpreted as an alpha value; that is, density 0 is fully transparent, density 1 is fully opaque.
In the case of transparent pattern fill, the background of the pattern is either fully transparent or fully
opaque.
