class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">colorspec</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>will set a
new line color while leaving the existing dot-dash pattern unchanged.
<!--l. 13082--><p class="noindent" >In 3d mode (<span 
class="cmbx-10">splot </span>command), the special keyword <span 
class="cmbx-10">palette </span>is allowed as a shorthand for <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>linetype palette z<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>. The
color value corresponds to the z-value (elevation) of the splot, and varies smoothly along a line or
surface.
<!--l. 13086--><p class="noindent" >Examples: Suppose that the default lines for indices 1, 2, and 3 are red, green, and blue, respectively,
and the default point shapes for the same indices are a square, a cross, and a triangle, respectively.
