<a 
 id="Q1-1-614"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-309001"></a>
<!--l. 13388--><p class="noindent" >Control of the major (labelled) tics on all axes at once is possible with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set tics </span>command.
<!--l. 13391--><p class="noindent" >Fine control of the major (labelled) tics on all axes at once is possible with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set tics </span>command. The tics
may be turned off with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset tics </span>command, and may be turned on (the default state) with
<span 
class="cmbx-10">set tics</span>. Similar commands (by preceding &#8217;tics&#8217; by the axis name) control the major tics on a single
axis.
