<!--l. 14236--><p class="noindent" >Fine control of the major (labelled) tics on the x axis is possible with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set xtics </span>command. The tics may be
turned off with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">unset xtics </span>command, and may be turned on (the default state) with <span 
class="cmbx-10">set xtics</span>. Similar
commands control the major tics on the y, z, x2 and y2 axes.
