<!--l. 14258--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14261--><p class="noindent" >The same syntax applies to <span 
class="cmbx-10">ytics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">ztics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">x2tics</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">y2tics </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">cbtics</span>.
<!--l. 14263--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">axis </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">border </span>tells <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>to put the tics (both the tics themselves and the accompanying labels) along the axis
or the border, respectively. If the axis is very close to the border, the <span 
class="cmbx-10">axis </span>option will move the tic labels to outside
the border. The relevant margin settings will usually be sized badly by the automatic layout algorithm in this
case.
<!--l. 14269--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">mirror </span>tells <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>to put unlabelled tics at the same positions on the opposite border. <span 
class="cmbx-10">nomirror </span>does what you
think it does.
<!--l. 14272--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">in </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">out </span>change the tic marks to be drawn inwards or outwards.
<!--l. 14274--><p class="noindent" >With <span 
class="cmbx-10">scale</span>, the size of the tic marks can be adjusted. If <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>minor<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is not specified, it is 0.5*<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>major<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>. The default
size 1.0 for major tics and 0.5 for minor tics is requested by <span 
class="cmbx-10">scale default</span>.
<!--l. 14278--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">rotate </span>asks <span 
class="cmbx-10">gnuplot </span>to rotate the text through 90 degrees, which will be done if the terminal driver in use supports
text rotation. <span 
class="cmbx-10">norotate </span>cancels this. <span 
class="cmbx-10">rotate by </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">ang</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>asks for rotation by <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>ang<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>degrees, supported by some
terminal types.
<!--l. 14283--><p class="noindent" >The defaults are <span 
class="cmbx-10">border mirror norotate </span>for tics on the x and y axes, and <span 
class="cmbx-10">border nomirror norotate </span>for tics
on the x2 and y2 axes. For the z axis, the <span 
class="cmbsy-10">{</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">axis </span><span 
class="cmsy-10">| </span><span 
class="cmbx-10">border</span><span 
class="cmbsy-10">} </span>option is not available and the default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">nomirror</span>. If
you do want to mirror the z-axis tics, you might want to create a bit more room for them with <span 
class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">border</span>.
<!--l. 14289--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>offset<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is specified by either x,y or x,y,z, and may be preceded by <span 
class="cmbx-10">first</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">second</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">graph</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">screen</span>, or
<span 
class="cmbx-10">character </span>to select the coordinate system. <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>offset<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is the offset of the tics texts from their default positions, while
the default coordinate system is <span 
class="cmbx-10">character</span>. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">coordinates (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-20000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">24</span><!--tex4ht:ref: coordinates --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-335003"></a> for details. <span 
class="cmbx-10">nooffset </span>switches off the
offset.
<!--l. 14295--><p class="noindent" >Example:
<!--l. 14297--><p class="noindent" >Move xtics more closely to the plot. <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;offset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,graph</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0.05</span>
<!--l. 14301--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14304--><p class="noindent" >By default, tic labels are justified automatically depending on the axis and rotation angle to produce aesthetically
pleasing results. If this is not desired, justification can be overridden with an explicit <span 
class="cmbx-10">left</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">right </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">center </span>keyword.
<span 
class="cmbx-10">autojustify </span>restores the default behavior.
<!--l. 14309--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">set xtics </span>with no options restores the default border or axis if xtics are being displayed; otherwise it has no effect.
Any previously specified tic frequency or position <span 
class="cmsy-10">{</span>and labels<span 
class="cmsy-10">} </span>are retained.
<!--l. 14313--><p class="noindent" >Positions of the tics are calculated automatically by default or if the <span 
class="cmbx-10">autofreq </span>option is given; otherwise they may
be specified in either of two forms:
<!--l. 14317--><p class="noindent" >The implicit <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>incr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>end<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>form specifies that a series of tics will be plotted on the axis between
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
the values <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>end<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>with an increment of <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>incr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>. If <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>end<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is not given, it is assumed
to be infinity. The increment may be negative. If neither <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>nor <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>end<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is given, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is
assumed to be negative infinity, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>end<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is assumed to be positive infinity, and the tics will be drawn at
integral multiples of <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>incr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>. If the axis is logarithmic, the increment will be used as a multiplicative
factor.
<!--l. 14325--><p class="noindent" >If you specify to a negative <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>or <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>incr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>after a numerical value (e.g., <span 
class="cmbx-10">rotate by </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">angle</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">offset</span>
<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">offset</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>), the parser fails because it subtracts <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>or <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>incr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>from that value. As a workaround, specify
<span 
class="cmbx-10">0-</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">start</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>resp. <span 
class="cmbx-10">0-</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">incr</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>in that case.
<!--l. 14330--><p class="noindent" >Example: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;border</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;offset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,0.5</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;-5,1,5</span>
<!--l. 14334--><p class="noindent" ></pre> Fails with &#8217;invalid expression&#8217; at the last comma. <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;border</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;offset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,0.5</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0-5,1,5</span>
<!--l. 14340--><p class="noindent" ></pre> or <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;offset</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,0.5</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;border</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;-5,1,5</span>
<!--l. 14346--><p class="noindent" ></pre> Sets tics at the border, tics text with an offset of 0,0.5 characters, and sets the start, increment, and end to -5, 1,
and 5, as requested.
<!--l. 14351--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set grid </span>options &#8217;front&#8217;, &#8217;back&#8217; and &#8217;layerdefault&#8217; affect the drawing order of the xtics, too.
<!--l. 14354--><p class="noindent" >Examples:
<!--l. 14356--><p class="noindent" >Make tics at 0, 0.5, 1, 1.5, ..., 9.5, 10. <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,.5,10</span>
<!--l. 14360--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14363--><p class="noindent" >Make tics at ..., -10, -5, 0, 5, 10, ... <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;5</span>
<!--l. 14367--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14370--><p class="noindent" >Make tics at 1, 100, 1e4, 1e6, 1e8. <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;logscale</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;x;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1,100,1e8</span>
<!--l. 14374--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14377--><p class="noindent" >The explicit (<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>label<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>pos<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; &#x003C;</span>level<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, ...) form allows arbitrary tic positions or non-numeric tic labels. In this
form, the tics do not need to be listed in numerical order. Each tic has a position, optionally with a label. Note that
the label is a string enclosed by quotes. It may be a constant string, such as <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>hello<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, may contain formatting
information for converting the position into its label, such as <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>%3f clients<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, or may be empty, <span 
class="cmtt-10">""</span>.
See <span 
class="cmbx-10">set format (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-221000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">152</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set format --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-335004"></a> for more information. If no string is given, the default label (numerical) is
used.
<!--l. 14387--><p class="noindent" >An explicit tic mark has a third parameter, the <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>level<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>. The default is level 0, a major tic. A level of 1 generates a
minor tic. If the level is specified, then the label must also be supplied.
<!--l. 14391--><p class="noindent" >Examples: <pre class="prettyprint">
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;("low"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"medium"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;50,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"high"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;100)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(1,2,4,8,16,32,64,128,256,512,1024)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ytics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;("bottom"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;""</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;10,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"top"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;20)</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ytics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;("bottom"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;""</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;10</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"top"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;20)</span>
<!--l. 14398--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14401--><p class="noindent" >In the second example, all tics are labelled. In the third, only the end tics are labelled. In the fourth, the unlabeled
tic is a minor tic.
<!--l. 14404--><p class="noindent" >Normally if explicit tics are given, they are used instead of auto-generated tics. Conversely if you specify
<span 
class="cmbx-10">set xtics auto </span>or the like it will erase any previously specified explicit tics. You can mix explicit
and auto- generated tics by using the keyword <span 
class="cmbx-10">add</span>, which must appear before the tic style being
added.
<!--l. 14410--><p class="noindent" >Example: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;0,.5,10</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;add</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;("Pi"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;3.14159)</span>
<!--l. 14415--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14418--><p class="noindent" >This will automatically generate tic marks every 0.5 along x, but will also add an explicit labeled tic mark at
pi.
<!--l. 14421--><p class="noindent" >However they are specified, tics will only be plotted when in range.
<!--l. 14423--><p class="noindent" >Format (or omission) of the tic labels is controlled by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set format</span>, unless the explicit text of a label is included in
the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set xtics (</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">label</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">) </span>form.
<!--l. 14426--><p class="noindent" >Minor (unlabelled) tics can be added automatically by the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set mxtics </span>command, or at explicit positions by the <span 
class="cmbx-10">set</span>
<span 
class="cmbx-10">xtics (</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"" </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">pos</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span><span 
class="cmbx-10">1, ...) </span>form.
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-336000III"></a>Xtics time_data</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-668"></a>
<!--l. 14433--><p class="noindent" >In case of timeseries data, axis tic position values must be given as quoted dates or times according to the format
<span 
class="cmbx-10">timefmt</span>. If the <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>incr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>end<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>form is used, <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>start<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>end<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>must be given according to <span 
class="cmbx-10">timefmt</span>,
but <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>incr<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>must be in seconds. Times will be written out according to the format given on <span 
class="cmbx-10">set format</span>,
however.
<!--l. 14439--><p class="noindent" >Examples: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xdata</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;time</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;timefmt</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"%d/%m"</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;format</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"%b</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;%d"</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xrange</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;["01/12":"06/12"]</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"01/12",</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;172800,</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"05/12"</span>
<!--l. 14447--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 14451--><p class="noindent" ><pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xdata</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;time</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;timefmt</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"%d/%m"</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;format</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"%b</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;%d"</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xrange</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;["01/12":"06/12"]</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xtics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;("01/12",</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;""</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"03/12",</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"05/12")</span>
<!--l. 14457--><p class="noindent" ></pre> Both of these will produce tics <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 1<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 3<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, and <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 5<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, but in the second example the tic at <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>Dec 3<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>will be
unlabelled.
<h5 class="likesubsubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-337000III"></a>Xtics rangelimited</h5>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-670"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-337001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-337002"></a>
<!--l. 14469--><p class="noindent" >This option limits both the auto-generated axis tic labels and the corresponding plot border to the range of
values actually present in the data that has been plotted. Note that this is independent of the current
range limits for the plot. For example, suppose that the data in <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>file.dat<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>all lies in the range 2 <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C; </span>y
<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C; </span>4. Then the following commands will create a plot for which the left-hand plot border (y axis) is
drawn for only this portion of the total y range, and only the axis tics in this region are generated.
I.e., the plot will be scaled to the full range on y, but there will be a gap between 0 and 2 on the left
border and another gap between 4 and 10. This style is sometimes referred to as a <span 
class="cmbx-10">range-frame </span>graph.
<pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;border</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;3</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;yrange</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;[0:10]</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ytics</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;nomirror</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;rangelimited</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;plot</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"file.dat"</span>
<!--l. 14485--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-338000III"></a>Xyplane</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-672"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-338001"></a>
<!--l. 14495--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">set xyplane </span>command adjusts the position at which the xy plane is drawn in a 3D plot. The synonym <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>set
ticslevel<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>is accepted for backwards compatibility.
<!--l. 14499--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xyplane</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;at</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;zvalue&#x003E;</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;xyplane</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;relative</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;frac&#x003E;</span>
<span 
