<!--l. 15408--><p class="noindent" >It may be convenient to track the statistics from more than one file at the same time. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">name </span>option causes the
default prefix <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>STATS<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>to be replaced by a user-specified string. For example, the mean value of column 2 data
from two different files could be compared by <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;stats</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"file1.dat"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;name</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"A"</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;stats</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"file2.dat"</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;using</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;2</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;name</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"B"</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;if</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;(A_mean</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;B_mean)</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{...}</span>
<!--l. 15417--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 15420--><p class="noindent" >The index reported in STATS_index_xxx corresponds to the value of pseudo-column 0 ($0) in plot commands. I.e.
the first point has index 0, the last point has index N-1.
<!--l. 15424--><p class="noindent" >Data values are sorted to find the median and quartile boundaries. If the total number of points N is odd,
then the median value is taken as the value of data point (N+1)/2. If N is even, then the median is
reported as the mean value of points N/2 and (N+2)/2. Equivalent treatment is used for the quartile
boundaries.
<!--l. 15430--><p class="noindent" >For an example of using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">stats </span>command to help annotate a subsequent plot, see
<!--l. 15432--><p class="noindent" >     <a 
href="http://www.gnuplot.info/demo/stats.html" ><span 
class="cmtt-10">stats.dem. </span></a>
<!--l. 15436--><p class="noindent" >The current implementation does not allow analysis if either the X or Y axis is set to log-scaling. This restriction
may be removed in a later version.
