<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-412000IV"></a>Dxf</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-819"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-412001"></a>
<!--l. 16703--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">dxf </span>terminal driver creates pictures that can be imported into AutoCad (Release 10.x). It has no options of its
own, but some features of its plots may be modified by other means. The default size is 120x80 AutoCad units,
which can be changed by <span 
class="cmbx-10">set size</span>. <span 
class="cmbx-10">dxf </span>uses seven colors (white, red, yellow, green, cyan, blue and magenta),
which can be changed only by modifying the source file. If a black-and-white plotting device is used,
the colors are mapped to differing line thicknesses. See the description of the AutoCad print/plot
command.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-413000IV"></a>Dxy800a</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-821"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-413001"></a>
<!--l. 16720--><p class="noindent" >This terminal driver supports the Roland DXY800A plotter. It has no options.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-414000IV"></a>Eepic</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-823"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-414001"></a>
<!--l. 16730--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">eepic </span>terminal driver supports the extended LaTeX picture environment. It is an alternative to the <span 
class="cmbx-10">latex</span>
driver.
<!--l. 16733--><p class="noindent" >The output of this terminal is intended for use with the <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>eepic.sty<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>macro package for LaTeX. To use it, you need
<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>eepic.sty<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>epic.sty<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>and a printer driver that supports the <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>tpic<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span><span 
class="cmsy-10">\</span>specials. If your printer driver doesn&#8217;t support
those <span 
class="cmsy-10">\</span>specials, <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>eepicemu.sty<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>will enable you to use some of them. dvips and dvipdfm do support the <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>tpic<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>
<span 
class="cmsy-10">\</span>specials.
<!--l. 16740--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;terminal</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;eepic</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{default}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{color|dashed}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{rotate}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;XX,YY}</span>
<span 
