<!--l. 16857--><p class="noindent" >In <span 
class="cmbx-10">monochrome </span>mode successive line types cycle through dash patterns. In <span 
class="cmbx-10">color </span>mode successive line types use
successive colors, and only after all 8 default colors are exhausted is the dash pattern incremented. <span 
class="cmbx-10">solid </span>draws all
curves with solid lines, overriding any dashed patterns; <span 
class="cmbx-10">linewidth </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">factor</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>multiplies all line widths by this
factor. <span 
class="cmbx-10">dashlength </span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">factor</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is useful for thick lines. <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>fontname<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is the name of a font; and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">fontsize</span><span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is the
size of the font in points.
<!--l. 16866--><p class="noindent" >The nominal size of the output image defaults to 1024x768 in arbitrary units. You may specify a different nominal
size using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">size </span>option.
<!--l. 16869--><p class="noindent" >Enhanced text mode tries to approximate proportional character spacing. If you are using a monospaced font, or
don&#8217;t like the approximation, you can turn off this correction using the <span 
class="cmbx-10">noproportional </span>option.
<!--l. 16873--><p class="noindent" >The default settings are <span 
class="cmbx-10">color dashed font </span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">Arial,12</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span><span 
class="cmbx-10">size 1024,768 </span>Selecting <span 
class="cmbx-10">default </span>sets all options to their
default values.
