<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-422000IV"></a>Ggi</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-839"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-422001"></a>
<!--l. 17447--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">ggi </span>driver can run on different targets as X or svgalib.
<!--l. 17449--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;terminal</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ggi</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;[acceleration</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;integer&#x003E;]</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;[[mode]</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{mode}]</span>
<!--l. 17453--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 17456--><p class="noindent" >In X the window cannot be resized using window manager handles, but the mode can be given with the mode
option, e.g.: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">-</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;V1024x768</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">-</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;V800x600</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">-</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;V640x480</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">-</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;V320x200</span>
<!--l. 17464--><p class="noindent" ></pre> Please refer to the ggi documentation for other modes. The &#8217;mode&#8217; keyword is optional. It is recommended to select
the target by environment variables as explained in the libggi manual page. To get DGA on X, you should for
example <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;bash&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;export</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;GGI_DISPLAY=DGA</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;csh&#x003E;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;setenv</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;GGI_DISPLAY</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;DGA</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 17474--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 17477--><p class="noindent" >&#8217;acceleration&#8217; is only used for targets which report relative pointer motion events (e.g. DGA) and is a
strictly positive integer multiplication factor for the relative distances. The default for acceleration is
7.
<!--l. 17481--><p class="noindent" >Examples: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;term</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ggi</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;acc</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;10</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;term</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ggi</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;acc</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;1</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;mode</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;V1024x768</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;term</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;ggi</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;V1024x768</span>
