<!--l. 17973--><p class="noindent" >PNG, JPEG and GIF images are created using the external library libgd. In most cases, PNG is to be preferred for
single plots, and GIF for animations. Both are loss-less image formats, and produce better image quality than the
lossy JPEG format. This is in particular noticeable for solid color lines against a solid background, i.e. exactly the
sort of image typically created by gnuplot.
<!--l. 17980--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">interlace </span>option creates a progressive JPEG image. Default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">nointerlace</span>.
<!--l. 17983--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">linewidth </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">dashlength </span>options are scaling factors that affect all lines drawn, i.e. they are multiplied by
values requested in various drawing commands.
<!--l. 17987--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">butt </span>instructs the driver to use a line drawing method that does not overshoot the desired end point of a line. This
setting is only applicable for line widths greater than 1. This setting is most useful when drawing horizontal or
vertical lines. Default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">rounded</span>.
<!--l. 17992--><p class="noindent" >The details of font selection are complicated. Two equivalent simple examples are given below: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;term</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;jpeg</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;font</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;arial</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;11</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><br /><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;term</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;jpeg</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;font</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;"arial,11"</span>
<!--l. 17998--><p class="noindent" ></pre> For more information please see the separate section under <span 
class="cmbx-10">fonts (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-36000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">37</span><!--tex4ht:ref: fonts --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-434002"></a>.
<!--l. 18002--><p class="noindent" >The output plot size <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>x,y<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is given in pixels &#8212; it defaults to 640x480. Please see additional information under
<span 
class="cmbx-10">canvas (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-17000I"><span 
class="cmbx-10">23</span><!--tex4ht:ref: canvas --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-434003"></a> and <span 
class="cmbx-10">set size (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-292000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">197</span><!--tex4ht:ref: set size --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-434004"></a>. Blank space at the edges of the finished plot may be trimmed using the
<span 
class="cmbx-10">crop </span>option, resulting in a smaller final image size. Default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">nocrop</span>.
<!--l. 18007--><p class="noindent" >The background color must be given in the form &#8217;xrrggbb&#8217;, where x is the literal character &#8217;x&#8217; and &#8217;rrggbb&#8217; are the
red, green and blue components in hexadecimal. For example, &#8217;x00ff00&#8217; is green. The specification of additional
colors other than the background is deprecated.
<!--l. 18012--><p class="noindent" >
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-435000IV"></a>Kyo</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-865"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-435001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-435002"></a>
<!--l. 18028--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">kyo </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">prescribe </span>terminal drivers support the Kyocera laser printer. The only difference between the two is
that <span 
class="cmbx-10">kyo </span>uses <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>Helvetica<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>whereas <span 
class="cmbx-10">prescribe </span>uses <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>Courier<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>. There are no options.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-436000IV"></a>Latex</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-867"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-436001"></a>
<a 
