<!--l. 18148--><p class="noindent" >A &#8217;target name&#8217; or &#8217;file name&#8217; (in quotes) for a script is mandatory. If a &#8217;target name&#8217; for the script is given, the
terminal will look for <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>gnuplot-<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>target name<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>.lua<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>in the local directory and on failure in the environmental
variable GNUPLOT_LUA_DIR.
<!--l. 18153--><p class="noindent" >All arguments will be provided to the selected script for further evaluation. E.g. &#8217;set term lua tikz help&#8217; will cause
the script itself to print additional help on options and choices for the script.
