class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;terminal</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;pbm</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{&#x003C;fontsize&#x003E;}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{&#x003C;mode&#x003E;}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{size</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;&#x003C;x&#x003E;,&#x003C;y&#x003E;}</span>
<!--l. 18863--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 18866--><p class="noindent" >where <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>fontsize<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is <span 
class="cmbx-10">small</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">medium</span>, or <span 
class="cmbx-10">large </span>and <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>mode<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>is <span 
class="cmbx-10">monochrome</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">gray </span>or <span 
class="cmbx-10">color</span>. The default plot size
is 640 pixels wide and 480 pixels high. The output size is white-space padded to the nearest multiple of 8 pixels on
both x and y. This empty space may be cropped later if needed.
<!--l. 18871--><p class="noindent" >The output of the <span 
class="cmbx-10">pbm </span>driver depends upon <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>mode<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E;</span>: <span 
class="cmbx-10">monochrome </span>produces a portable bitmap (one bit per
pixel), <span 
class="cmbx-10">gray </span>a portable graymap (three bits per pixel) and <span 
class="cmbx-10">color </span>a portable pixmap (color, four bits per
pixel).
<!--l. 18875--><p class="noindent" >The output of this driver can be used with various image conversion and manipulation utilities provided by
NETPBM. Based on Jef Poskanzer&#8217;s PBMPLUS package, NETPBM provides programs to convert the above PBM
formats to GIF, TIFF, MacPaint, Macintosh PICT, PCX, X11 bitmap and many others. Complete information is
available at http://netpbm.sourceforge.net/.
