class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;png:-&#8217;</span>
<!--l. 19101--><p class="noindent" ></pre> You can view the output from successive plot commands interactively by typing <span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003C;</span>space<span 
class="cmmi-10">&#x003E; </span>in the display window. To
save the current plot to a file, left click in the display window and choose <span 
class="cmbx-10">save</span>.
<!--l. 19107--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">transparent </span>instructs the driver to make the background color transparent. Default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">notransparent</span>.
<!--l. 19110--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">interlace </span>instructs the driver to generate interlaced PNGs. Default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">nointerlace</span>.
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 19113--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">linewidth </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">dashlength </span>options are scaling factors that affect all lines drawn, i.e. they are multiplied by
values requested in various drawing commands.
<!--l. 19117--><p class="noindent" >By default output png images use 256 indexed colors. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">truecolor </span>option instead creates TrueColor images with
24 bits of color information per pixel. Transparent fill styles require the <span 
class="cmbx-10">truecolor </span>option. See <span 
class="cmbx-10">fillstyle (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-297000III"><span 
class="cmbx-10">202</span><!--tex4ht:ref: fillstyle --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-452002"></a>. A
transparent background is possible in either indexed or TrueColor images.
<!--l. 19122--><p class="noindent" ><span 
class="cmbx-10">butt </span>instructs the driver to use a line drawing method that does not overshoot the desired end point of a line. This
setting is only applicable for line widths greater than 1. This setting is most useful when drawing horizontal or
vertical lines. Default is <span 
class="cmbx-10">rounded</span>.
<!--l. 19127--><p class="noindent" >The details of font selection are complicated. Two equivalent simple examples are given below: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
