<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-461000IV"></a>Pstricks</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-917"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-461001"></a>
<!--l. 19799--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">pstricks </span>driver is intended for use with the <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>pstricks.sty<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>macro package for LaTeX. It is an alternative to the
<span 
class="cmbx-10">eepic </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">latex </span>drivers. You need <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>pstricks.sty<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>, and, of course, a printer that understands PostScript, or a
converter such as Ghostscript.
<!--l. 19804--><p class="noindent" >PSTricks is available via anonymous ftp from the /pub directory at Princeton.edu. This driver definitely does not
come close to using the full capability of the PSTricks package.
<!--l. 19808--><p class="noindent" >Syntax: <pre class="prettyprint">
<span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;set</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;terminal</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;pstricks</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{hacktext</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;nohacktext}</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;{unit</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;|</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">&#x00A0;nounit}</span>
                                                                                         
                                                                                         
<!--l. 19812--><p class="noindent" ></pre>
<!--l. 19815--><p class="noindent" >The first option invokes an ugly hack that gives nicer numbers; the second has to do with plot scaling. The defaults
are <span 
class="cmbx-10">hacktext </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">nounit</span>.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-462000IV"></a>Qms</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-919"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-462001"></a>
<!--l. 19826--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">qms </span>terminal driver supports the QMS/QUIC Laser printer, the Talaris 1200 and others. It has no
options.
