 id="dx1-468001"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-468002"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-468003"></a>
<!--l. 20053--><p class="noindent" >This family of terminal drivers supports a variety of VT-like terminals. <span 
class="cmbx-10">tek40xx </span>supports Tektronix 4010 and
others as well as most TEK emulators. <span 
class="cmbx-10">vttek </span>supports VT-like tek40xx terminal emulators. The following are
present only if selected when gnuplot is built: <span 
class="cmbx-10">kc-tek40xx </span>supports MS-DOS Kermit Tek4010 terminal emulators in
color; <span 
class="cmbx-10">km-tek40xx </span>supports them in monochrome. <span 
class="cmbx-10">selanar </span>supports Selanar graphics. <span 
class="cmbx-10">bitgraph </span>supports BBN
Bitgraph terminals. None have any options.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-469000IV"></a>Tek410x</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-933"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-469001"></a>
<!--l. 20070--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">tek410x </span>terminal driver supports the 410x and 420x family of Tektronix terminals. It has no
options.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-470000IV"></a>Texdraw</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-935"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-470001"></a>
<!--l. 20081--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">texdraw </span>terminal driver supports the LaTeX texdraw environment. It is intended for use with <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>texdraw.sty<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>
and <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>texdraw.tex<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>in the texdraw package.
<!--l. 20084--><p class="noindent" >Points, among other things, are drawn using the LaTeX commands <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">\</span>Diamond<span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span>and <span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmsy-10">\</span>Box<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>. These commands
no longer belong to the LaTeX2e core; they are included in the latexsym package, which is part of
the base distribution and thus part of any LaTeX implementation. Please do not forget to use this
package.
<!--l. 20089--><p class="noindent" >It has no options.
<h4 class="likesubsectionHead"><a 
 id="x1-471000IV"></a>Tgif</h4>
<a 
 id="Q1-1-937"></a>
<a 
 id="dx1-471001"></a>
<!--l. 20099--><p class="noindent" >Tgif is an X11-based drawing tool &#8212; it has nothing to do with GIF.
<!--l. 20101--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">tgif </span>driver supports different pointsizes (with <span 
class="cmbx-10">set pointsize</span>), different label fonts and font sizes (e.g. <span 
class="cmbx-10">set label</span>
<span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">Hallo</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">" </span><span 
class="cmbx-10">at x,y font </span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">Helvetica,34</span><span 
class="cmtt-10">"</span>) and multiple graphs on the page. The proportions of the axes are not
changed.
