<!--l. 20661--><p class="noindent" >These settings apply to the wgnuplot text-window only. The <span 
class="cmbx-10">TextOrigin </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">TextSize </span>entries specify the location
and size of the text window.
<!--l. 20665--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">TextFont </span>entry specifies the text window font and size.
<!--l. 20667--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">TextWrap </span>entry selects wrapping of long text lines.
<!--l. 20669--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">TextLines </span>entry specifies the number of (unwrapped) lines the internal buffer of the text window can hold.
This value currently cannot be changed from within wgnuplot.
<!--l. 20673--><p class="noindent" >See <span 
class="cmbx-10">text-menu (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-481000IV"><span 
class="cmbx-10">306</span><!--tex4ht:ref: text-menu --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-483002"></a>.
<!--l. 20676--><p class="noindent" >The <span 
class="cmbx-10">GraphFont </span>entry specifies the font name and size in points.
<!--l. 20678--><p class="noindent" >The five numbers given in the <span 
class="cmbx-10">Border</span>, <span 
class="cmbx-10">Axis </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">Line </span>entries are the <span 
class="cmbx-10">Red </span>intensity (0&#8211;255), <span 
class="cmbx-10">Green </span>intensity,
<span 
class="cmbx-10">Blue </span>intensity, <span 
class="cmbx-10">Color Linestyle </span>and <span 
class="cmbx-10">Mono Linestyle</span>. <span 
class="cmbx-10">Linestyles </span>are 0=SOLID, 1=DASH, 2=DOT,
3=DASHDOT, 4=DASHDOTDOT. In the sample <span 
class="cmbx-10">wgnuplot.ini </span>file above, Line 2 is a green solid line in color
mode, or a dashed line in monochrome mode. The default line width is 1 pixel. If <span 
class="cmbx-10">Linestyle </span>is negative, it specifies
the width of a SOLID line in pixels. Line1 and any linestyle used with the <span 
class="cmbx-10">points </span>style must be SOLID with unit
width.
<!--l. 20688--><p class="noindent" >See <span 
class="cmbx-10">graph-menu (p.</span><span 
class="cmbx-10">&#x00A0;</span><a 
href="#x1-479000IV"><span 
class="cmbx-10">305</span><!--tex4ht:ref: graph-menu --></a><span 
class="cmbx-10">)</span><a 
 id="dx1-483003"></a>.
