<!--l. 21302--><p class="noindent" >By default the contents of the current plot window are exported to the X11 clipboard in response to
X events in the window. Setting the resource &#8217;gnuplot*exportselection&#8217; to &#8217;off&#8217; or &#8217;false&#8217; will disable
this.
<!--l. 21306--><p class="noindent" >By default text rotation is done using a method that is fast, but can corrupt nearby colors depending on the
background. If this is a problem, you can set the resource &#8217;gnuplot.fastrotate&#8217; to &#8217;off&#8217;
